title: Another Gaza hospital caught in fighting, as storms deepen civilian misery
description: Strikes against Gaza’s Indonesian hospital in the north and residential neighborhoods in the south have left an increasingly miserable population with few places to hide.

title: Who is Javier Milei, Argentina’s far-right president-elect?
description: Argentina’s next president will be Javier Milei, a libertarian economist who embraces comparisons to Donald Trump and promises to take down the establishment.

title: Austin visits Kyiv as worries rise over U.S. military funding
description: Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin made his second visit to the capital of Ukraine since Russia’s invasion as the Biden administration pledges aid will continue.

title: Napoleon’s hats were a fashion statement. One has sold for $2.1 million.
description: The cracked black beaver felt hat is one of approximately 20 that remain from Napoleon’s collection.

title: Brazil reckons with dark side of açaí: Rampant, dangerous child labor
description: After a Washington Post report drew international attention, authorities are investigating the industry. They’ve documented paralysis, spinal and skeletal injuries and venomous snake bites.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Israel claims footage shows hostages at al-Shifa; Hamas says video is ‘in our favor’
description: The IDF released footage it said proves Hamas was “forcibly transporting hostages” on Oct. 7 through al-Shifa Hospital. Hamas said it shows captives receive medical care.
